[The new LSD outbreak in Nea Kessani, extending the dimensions of the epizootic considerably westwards, has been reported to the OIE in Greece's follow-up report No 3, submitted to the OIE on 27 Sep 2015. Its location can be seen in the map appended to the report, at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?reportid=18731.

The report includes information on 31 other new outbreaks closer to the Turkish border in the east; in total, the 32 affected farms included 2226 susceptible cattle, of which 214 were clinical cases, and 2 were deaths. 2224 head of cattle were culled in accordance with the prevailing stamping-out policy.

Since the start of the LSD epizootic in Greece, reportedly on 18 Aug 2015, 56 outbreaks have been reported.

Outbreak summary:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3906 / 362 / 7 / 3899 / 0

An emergency vaccination campaign of cattle against LSD throughout the entire Evros regional unit is in progress as of 5 Sep 2015. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3676844,83.]
